nodes.title: ControlNet Slider Note
widgets_values:
Higher value means more strength of your Flux "ControlNet" tools model. This can be set to a maximum of your steps.
So if maximum steps is 20, ControlNet slider max is 20.

If maximum steps is 30, ControlNet slider max is 30.

Assumptions / Notes
- Can skip the Qwen VL prompt generation and manually enter prompt
- ControlNet strength can be controlled with ControlNet Slider
- styles.csv is included in the repo. It works with the custom node "WAS Node Suite (Revised)". To use the styls.csv go to ComfyUI install folder to and then custom_nodes and look for was-ns folder.  In that folder there is a was_suite_config.json file edit that file with Notepad.  Lok for the "webui_styles" line and put the path location to the styles.csv.  Example: "webui_styles": "D:\\StabilityMatrix\\Packages\\ComfyUI\\styles.csv",
- After configuring the styles.csv you will see tons of styles in the Styles Selector node
